    {
      "id": "431ec94c-4c53-4661-8fb0-2ce7bdee61b1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Authors use semi-supervised learning to predict final exam grades at the end of the academic year in undergraduate students using data from 3 different sources. Authors use a dataset provided by Hellenic Open University comparing approach against well-established ML algorithms. Results show good performance on early detection with small amounts of data.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
